From: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@wdc.com>
Date: Tue, 26 Jun 2018 20:56:55 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] ata: Fix ZBC_OUT all bit handling
References: bnc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 4.17.7
Git-commit: 6edf1d4cb0acde3a0a5dac849f33031bd7abb7b1

commit 6edf1d4cb0acde3a0a5dac849f33031bd7abb7b1 upstream.

If the ALL bit is set in the ZBC_OUT command, the command zone ID field
(block) should be ignored.

Reported-by: David Butterfield <david.butterfield@wdc.com>
Signed-off-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@wdc.com>
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Tejun Heo <tj@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 drivers/ata/libata-scsi.c | 11 ++++++++---
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/ata/libata-scsi.c b/drivers/ata/libata-scsi.c
index fb5c99156410..c0ac1ea3e7a3 100644
--- a/drivers/ata/libata-scsi.c
+++ b/drivers/ata/libata-scsi.c
@@ -3802,7 +3802,14 @@ static unsigned int ata_scsi_zbc_out_xlat(struct ata_queued_cmd *qc)
 		 */
 		goto invalid_param_len;
 	}
-	if (block >= dev->n_sectors) {
+
+	all = cdb[14] & 0x1;
+	if (all) {
+		/*
+		 * Ignore the block address (zone ID) as defined by ZBC.
+		 */
+		block = 0;
+	} else if (block >= dev->n_sectors) {
 		/*
 		 * Block must be a valid zone ID (a zone start LBA).
 		 */
@@ -3810,8 +3817,6 @@ static unsigned int ata_scsi_zbc_out_xlat(struct ata_queued_cmd *qc)
 		goto invalid_fld;
 	}
 
-	all = cdb[14] & 0x1;
-
 	if (ata_ncq_enabled(qc->dev) &&
 	    ata_fpdma_zac_mgmt_out_supported(qc->dev)) {
 		tf->protocol = ATA_PROT_NCQ_NODATA;
